🔍 Troubleshooting Guide (Real Errors)
❌ ERROR 1
MySQL Connection Error
MySQLdb.OperationalError:
Can't connect to local server through socket
'/run/mysqld/mysqld.sock'
📌 Root Cause

Application trying to connect to localhost MySQL socket instead of MySQL container.

✅ Solution

Use MySQL container name as host.

MYSQL_HOST=mysql

Correct run command:

docker run -d \
-p 5000:5000 \
--network flask-network \
-e MYSQL_HOST=mysql \
-e MYSQL_USER=root \
-e MYSQL_PASSWORD=root \
-e MYSQL_DB=devops \
two-tier-flask:v1
❌ ERROR 2
Unknown Database
MySQLdb.OperationalError: (1049, "Unknown database 'devops'")
📌 Root Cause

Database not created in MySQL container.

✅ Solution

Create database manually.

Enter container:

docker exec -it mysql mysql -u root -p

Create database:

CREATE DATABASE devops;

Verify:

SHOW DATABASES;
❌ ERROR 3
Wrong environment variable syntax

Incorrect command:

-e MYSQL_HOST = mysql
📌 Problem

Spaces around = break environment variable parsing.

✅ Correct
-e MYSQL_HOST=mysql
❌ ERROR 4
MySQL command not working inside container

You ran:

SHOW DATABASES;

inside bash shell.

📌 Problem

MySQL commands only work inside MySQL client.

✅ Correct way

Enter MySQL client:

mysql -u root -p

Then run:

SHOW DATABASES;
❌ ERROR 5
Python Package Build Failure

Error:

pkg-config: not found
ERROR: Failed to build mysqlclient
📌 Root Cause

System dependencies missing in base image.

✅ Fix Dockerfile
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y \
pkg-config \
default-libmysqlclient-dev \
build-essential
❌ ERROR 6
Flask Error (Python 3.14)
AttributeError: module 'pkgutil' has no attribute 'get_loader'
📌 Root Cause

Flask incompatible with Python 3.14.

✅ Solution

Use stable version:

FROM python:3.9-slim
