🚨 Real-World Production Incident Scenarios
Incident 1
Container keeps restarting

Check:

docker ps -a

Then logs:

docker logs container_id

Common reasons:

Missing env variables

DB connection failure

Missing dependency

Incident 2
App works locally but not in container

Debug:

docker exec -it container bash

Check installed packages:

pip list
Incident 3
Port not accessible

Check container port mapping:

docker ps

Example:

0.0.0.0:5000->5000/tcp

Test:

curl localhost:5000
Incident 4
DB container running but app cannot connect

Check network:

docker network inspect flask-network

Containers must be inside same network.

